Tentative spec => https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Y415qZcZQeKVsqZJ7gfH62pwOqQAAplXxcBSuvfOiV4/edit#heading=h.59m74p2xlbqq

Gist version (may go out of date) => https://gist.github.com/GrayHatter/409cae0c1f788b4eaeab9eaad695432b

comment_data.body: Do we have any basis for implementing this? The linked spec specifically mentions "distributed name resolution" as not being in scope.
Is reliable distributed naming resolution even technically possible? If so, are there references to existing solutions or white papers that cover that?
@cebe With a blockchain, certainly. Take a look at Namecoin. The issue is that we probably don't want a blockchain solution. Or do we?
@Zer0-One I consider private to be important as well. (Which is why I didn't include that in the TQNL spec)
Yeah I do not think a block chain would fit for tox.
Hi, I'm a Namecoin developer.  May I ask what your concerns would be with a blockchain-based solution?
I don't speak for everyone, but I don't have an issue with a blockchain solution; only basing our naming on a separate/existing blockchain.

Hi @GrayHatter,

> I don't speak for everyone, but I don't have an issue with a blockchain solution; only basing our naming on a separate/existing blockchain.

If I understand correctly you're suggesting using a Tox-specific blockchain?  IMHO this would be unwise, because the hashrate of such a blockchain would probably be too low to prevent 51% attacks effectively.

Cheers.

> If I understand correctly you're suggesting using a Tox-specific blockchain? 

No, I think that would be a bad idea. And you already covered why.

>IMHO this would be unwise, because the hashrate of such a blockchain would probably be too low to prevent 51% attacks effectively.

And the pair together; I don't want to use someone else's block chain, and the Sybil attack. I don't think there's a good solution inside a blockchain (not under the contemporary definition).

> May I ask what your concerns would be with a blockchain-based solution?

@JeremyRand it doesn't scale, and seems to be too costly when it comes to consuming resources.

I think this is very high priority, but should live outside toxcore itself. Toxcore can provide the functions to facilitate it, but I'd like to avoid adding complexity to core (we're already doing that with new group chats :\). If someone wants to work on this, I'm happy to create a new repo for that. I don't know where this issue should live in the meantime, so I'm closing it for now.
